cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper focuses on Named Entity Recognition (NER) for Nepali language using a neural-based approach, which falls under the scope of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed model is a neural-based approach, which falls under the scope of neural computing. 
- cs.LG (Learning): The proposed model is a machine learning approach, which falls under the scope of learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed model is an AI-based approach for NER, which falls under the scope of AI. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): NER is an important task in information retrieval, and the proposed model can be used to improve the performance of NER in Nepali language information retrieval systems.
